#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SEIS_ct.rst:4
#: d26efe5ea6934be98cf6fbf6f1b50d9f
msgid "The SEIS_ct Model assumes that infection spreads only through links between neighboring nodes in a graph :math:`G=(V,E)`. Each node is in one of three states: :math:`S` (susceptible), :math:`E` (exposed/incubating), or :math:`I` (infected). Compared with the discrete-step SEIS, **SEIS_ct uses elapsed-time–dependent transition probabilities** for :math:`E\\to I` and :math:`I\\to S` based on the time since the last state entry."
msgstr ""

